        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 27 at 7:20PM CDT until June 27 at 8:00PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>SVRBMX

The National Weather Service in Birmingham has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southwestern Jefferson County in central Alabama...

* Until 800 PM CDT.

* At 720 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Bull City to Splash Adventure, moving northeast
at 10 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Southwestern Birmingham, Bessemer, Hueytown, Fairfield, Pleasant
Grove, Midfield, Adamsville, Brighton, Lipscomb, Sylvan Springs,
Mulga, Maytown, West Jefferson, North Johns, Birmingham Fairgounds,
B.j.c.c., Edgewater, Ensley, Legion Field, and Forestdale.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
